<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-910-098  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 910 098.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Nov 27 1989 v6 n47 p14(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>3-D board transfers workstation images directly to videotape.andO;(Silicon Graphics Inc. to resell VME video board as Iris 4Dworkstation option) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bowen, Ted Smalley.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Silicon Graphics Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    SGIC.andO;Product:   Silicon Graphics VideoCreator (Graphics board) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     WorkstationsImaging TechnologyVideo BoardsThree-Dimensional Graphics.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>3-D Board Transfers Workstation Images Directly to VideotapeandM;MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif.andP;  -- Silicon Graphics has announced it will resell on anOEM basis a VME video board that lets users transfer high-resolution 3-Dimages directly from a workstation onto videotape.andM;The board will be sold as an option for the company's Iris 4D workstationsbut can also be used with other Silicon Graphics workstations, companyofficials said.andM;The triple-height board, called the VideoCreator, allows users to recordgraphics directly from a workstation onto standard videotape or diskrecorders in real time or frame by frame.andM;VideoCreator can record individual frames sequentially for computeranimation.andP;  It includes scan conversion for recording high-resolutionmonitors in real time.andM;The product is sold as a stand-alone box.andP;  VideoCreator is available in twoversions.andP;  One version provides RGB, NTSC and S-VHS formats, and the otherprovides RGB and PAL video formats.andM;VideoCreator was developed by Folsom Research of Folsom, Calif., andVideomedia of Sunnyvale, Calif.andP;  It uses Videomedia's V-LAN video machinecontrol interface.andM;Under the OEM agreement, Folsom Research will also sell the product, underthe name Video/9U, directly to its customers.andM;Silicon Graphics' VideoCreator will be available in the first quarter of nextyear and is priced at $9,950 for the board and $12,000 for the stand-aloneversion, including a SCSI interface.andM;Silicon Graphics Inc. is located at 2011 N. Shoreline Blvd., P.O. Box 7311,Mountain View, CA 94039-7311, (415) 960-1980.andO;</TEXT></DOC>